text: Ok I shouldn't have been surprised there would be comments saying "oh it's a hunger games ripoff!" After all after Twishit came out there's always assholes who cry ripoff to any vampire or werewolf show or movie as if Twishit invented them. I have read the hunger games books, which got me to read several other YA book series, I've been surprised at how good they were, I'm reading Divergent now. than I found out months ago that Dylan O Brian was set to star in this movie, so I got the first book. And let me tell u it is NOT like THG books or any of the other series. Whereas THG and Divergent are about Dystopian future societies and focus on fighting against the political corruption with sci if elemnents. But you know what is going I with the characters, and why they are in the life or death situations they face. TMR the reasons are completely unknown, it's straight up  mystery, sci fi and horror, I mean they are dark, violent and actually creeped me out many times to the point that I thought they could have been in the adult section of bookstores and libraries. text: Stop calling it a dystopia. Post-Apocalyptic and Dystopia are not the same thing. They can have similarities but people are throwing that name around when the story in question doesn't actually fit. A dystopia is about a flawed society and how that society doesn't work. An apocalyptic event can be the reason for why it formed. But it's not about the event itself. Maze Runner doesn't have some totalitarian government who do terrible things to stay in power like Hunger Games or Battle Royale. And it's not about society that creates unethical life-styles of how you will live, that they believe is perfect but isn't like Divergent or The Giver. It's about how scientists try to deal with a disease that was originally created to control the population after a sun-flare attack and destroyed most of the earth. And it's about the people used as subjects for these experiments realizing that they're subjects for experiments and try to escape.
